        "title": "Support z.ai BigModel team usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a z.ai usage scope for BigModel team quota requests while preserving the existing personal Coding Plan path.\n- Send `type=2` plus `Bigmodel-Organization` / `Bigmodel-Project` on team quota/model-usage requests, and wire the scope through app settings, config/env overrides, provider snapshots, and CLI settings.\n- Route BigModel CN team dashboard actions to `/coding-plan/team/usage-stats`.\n\n## Why\nBigModel team Coding Plan usage can return `ÕĮōÕēŹńö©µłĘõĖŹÕŁśÕ£©coding plan` when queried through the personal quota path. The team quota endpoint requires the team scope query parameter and organization/project headers. Existing z.ai fixes cover region selection, multi-limit parsing, and MCP labeling, but not the team usage scope/header path.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `swift test --filter ZaiProviderTests`\n- `swift test --filter ProviderConfigEnvironmentTests`\n- `swift test --filter TokenAccountEnvironmentPrecedenceTests`\n- `swift test --filter ZaiTokenAccountEnvironmentPrecedenceTests`\n- `swift test --filter ConfigValidationTests`\n- `swift test --filter 'CodexBarTests.StatusMenuTests/`zai dashboard action follows selected region`()'`\n- `swift test --filter 'persists zai team usage settings across instances'`\n- `swift build --product CodexBarCLI`\n- `swift build --product CodexBar`\n- `make check`\n- Live CLI smoke: `CodexBarCLI usage --provider zai --format json` with team scope env returned z.ai API usage windows without a provider error.\n- App smoke: launched local `CodexBar` product with a temporary z.ai team config for 6 seconds; process stayed running and produced no crash output.\n",
